<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/bug/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_generalform/generalform">

    <h1 tal:condition="view/label"
        tal:content="view/label"
        metal:fill-slot="heading">Add a branch</h1>

    <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info" class="documentDescription">
      <p tal:condition="context/bug/private"
           class="warning message">
        This bug is private. Only private branches should be linked to
        this bug.
     </p>

      Adding a Bazaar branch to a bug allows you to notify others
      about where work is going on to fix this bug.
    </div>

    <legend metal:fill-slot="form_legend">Add a Branch</legend>

  </div>

</div><tal:comment condition="nothing"><!-- end main slot --></tal:comment>

<metal:block fill-slot="help">

  <p>Launchpad is integrated with the <a
    href="http://bazaar-vcs.org/">Bazaar</a> version control system. (<a
    href="http://bazaar-vcs.org/WhyUseBzr">Why use Bazaar?</a>).</p>

  <p>Post this form to associate this bug to a Bazaar branch that is already
    known to Launchpad. This allows quickly locating branches that contain work
    to fix this bug.<p>

  <p>To specify the branch, you can paste its unique name (of the form
    ~owner/product/branch), its URL on <code>bazaar.launchpad.net</code>, or
    its external URL in the case of a mirror branch. You can also click on
    "Choose..." to search for a branch.</p>

  <p>Each bug-branch association has a status, initially "Fix In Progress" and a
    whiteboard that can be used to write short comments.</p>

</metal:block><tal:comment condition="nothing"><!-- end help slot --></tal:comment>
</body>

</html>

